(Description)
An ugly number is a positive integer which does not have a prime factor other than 2, 3, and 5.
Given an integer n, return true if n is an ugly number.

--- Solution ---
class Solution {
    public boolean isUgly(int n) {
        if (n <= 0) return false;
        boolean isUgly = false;

        while (n != 1 && !isUgly) {
            if (n % 2 == 0) {
                n /= 2;
            }
            else if (n % 3 == 0) {
                n /= 3;
            }
            else if (n % 5 == 0) {
                n /= 5;
            }
            else {
                isUgly = true;
            }
        }

        return (n == 1 ? true : false);
    }
}

--- Approach ---
- Until the given number become 1, the number was constantly divided by 2, 3, or 5, when it is possible.
- If the number was not divided by 2, 3, or 5, that means it have a another prime factor; the number is determined as a ugly number.
